programme.title: Sitting Bull
programme.desc: Major Robert Parrish becomes embroilled in the Battle of Little Big Horn. When he helps Chief Sitting Bull escape, he is charged with crimes against his government. Now facing possible execution, only President Ulysses S. Grant can help him.

programme.title: The Borrowers
programme.desc: A Primetime Emmy went to this production of Mary Norton's famous children's tale. It's all about a little boy (Dennis Larson) who discovers a family of tiny people living under the floorboards of his home. The cast includes Eddie Albert, Tammy Grimes, and Judith Anderson, plus the curmudgeonly Barnard Hughes.

programme.title: Hercules and the Captive Women
programme.desc: Originally released in 1961 as "Ercole alla conquista di Atlantide" in Italy, "Hercules and the Captive Women" is the updated US version released for audiences in 1963. Follow the chronicles of Hercules with Reg Park in his Hercules film debut! Action packed from the beginning, Hercules encounters Ismene (Laura Altan) when he must save her from a shape-shifting creature -- and that's just the beginning! Ismene then brings Hercules to Atlantis where they come face to face with the evil Queen Antinea (Fay Spain), Ismene's mother, and try to prevent her dreams of world conquest. Will Hercules prevail? Find out in "Hercules and the Captive Women."

programme.title: Condemned to Live
programme.desc: When a peaceful European village is suddenly plagued by a string of gruesome murders, the nocturnal attacks are pegged on a mysterious giant bat. But the real culprit is mild-mannered, respectable Paul Kristan, a kindly professor with an enigmatic ailment that transforms him nightly into a bloodthirsty vampire. Directed by horror aficionado Frank R. Strayer and produced independently, this film bears many of the hallmarks of a Universal prestige picture, and was a rarity for its time, considering its relatively sympathetic treatment of vampires.

programme.title: Episode 7
programme.desc: Groucho, Chico and Harpo graced the small screen in the 1950s appearing in a myriad of variety programs, sitcoms, and game shows. The Marx Brothers TV Collection features long-lost material from this wide array of appearances.

programme.title: Carol Burnett Show - Season 1 Episode 11
programme.desc: Guest starring Don Adams and Lesley Anne Warren in a series of comedic sketches hosted by Carol Burnett.

programme.title: Season 11 Episode 99
programme.desc: Comedian Johnny Carson hosts a variety of celebrities in his iconic late night talk show.

programme.title: Mysterious Mr. Wong
programme.desc: Out of the night creeps a shadow, striking terror into the heart of Chinatown! Bela Lugosi plays a power mad psychopath in this thriller from Monogram Pictures. William Nigh directs a tale of kidnapping and intrigue, with a cast that includes Wallace Ford (Freaks, Shadow of a Doubt) as a wiseguy reporter who falls into the diabolical clutches of the sinister Wong, a madman who believes he will one day rule China!

programme.title: Chamber of Horrors
programme.desc: A wealthy lord dies and is entombed with a valuable deposit of jewels. Seven keys are required to unlock the tomb and get hold of the treasure. A series of mysterious events cause the keys to be scattered, and when trying to unravel the circumstances, the heiress of the fortune and her companion investigators become entangled in a web of fraud, deceit, torture, and murder.

programme.title: Dark Night of the Scarecrow
programme.desc: When gentle but mentally challenged Bubba Ritter's young friend Marylee is mauled by a vicious dog, Bubba becomes the town scapegoat. Disguised as a scarecrow to hide from the angry townspeople, Bubba is found out and tragically murdered. But little do his attackers know that justice for Bubba will come from beyond the grave!

programme.title: Anatomy of a Psycho (1961)
programme.desc: Terrifying! A Psychotic Killer prowls the night! ... Will he be stopped before he kills again? Ronnie Burns (the son of TV favorites George Burns and Gracie Allen!) stars as Chet, a delusional young man boiling with rage after his brother is sentenced to death for murder. As his paranoid feelings increase, Chet decides to create some mayhem of his own, including arson! A cast of unknowns come together for this feature by Boris Petroff, who also directed the cult favorite, The Unearthly. Just sit back and enjoy watching poor Chet lose touch with reality!

programme.title: Nose (1958)
programme.desc: Here he is: the one, the only… GROUCHO! Legendary comedian, Groucho Marx, hosts this laugh-a-minute quiz show, where three couples face off, answering questions of varying difficulty. This game show is sure to make you laugh as contestants struggle to keep up with Marx’s lightning-quick wit and goofy antics.

programme.title: The Big Frame
programme.desc: A man is found dead in the gutter. At first it seems as a hit-run case, but Friday and Smith become suspicious when all witnesses from the night before give exactly the same story. Usually witnesses are at variance in some respects.

programme.title: The Hand
programme.desc: After murdering a young woman, a piano player discovers, to his horror, that no matter how hard he tries, he cannot remove the woman’s blood from his hands.

programme.title: The Bride (1959)
programme.desc: Immigrants are the target of a marriage racket and it’s up to Mike to stop them.

programme.title: The Spanish Grant
programme.desc: The Cartwrights try to invalidate a Spanish land grant to stop the De La Cuesta family from taking part of the Ponderosa and all of the Carson Valley settlers' land.

programme.title: The Psychiatrist gets Clampetted
programme.desc: Jethro finally gets his certificate from Dr. Twombly so he can graduate from the fifth grade, but Twombly wants to talk to Granny again.

programme.title: The Case of the Tyrant's Daughter
programme.desc: A chemist is accused of murdering his fiancé's stepfather, who was determined to keep the two apart. Although there is mounting evidence of the chemist's guilt, Holmes is requested by the the victim's housekeeper to investigate the case, as she believes the chemst to be innocent.

programme.title: Who Search for Truth
programme.desc: Medic follows Dr. Konrad Styner and his team of Surgeons as they tackle medical cases inside Los Angeles.

programme.title: The Joe Angelo Story
programme.desc: New York City police officer Barney Ruditsky faces off against organized crime during the Roaring 20s.

programme.title: The Celebrity
programme.desc: Stanley lies to Celia about having celebrity friends.

programme.title: Grandpa Jim's Rejuvenation
programme.desc: Jim reminisces about his college days and worries that his best years are behind him.

programme.title: Wacky Taxi
programme.desc: John Astin plays Pepper, a man who quits his job as a factory worker to go into business as a taxi driver. With his business being illegal, Pepper spends his days running from cops and scouting for fares. When his car is stolen, Pepper must get it back or risk losing everything.

programme.title: Dean's Place
programme.desc: Dean Martin is joined by Milton Berle, Angie Dickinson, Robert Mitchum, and more from his 1975 comedy/variety special.

programme.title: Hollywood Man
programme.desc: A film crew becomes desperate when their attempts to film a motorcycle scene keep being impeded by the local mafia.

programme.title: The Deadly Companions
programme.desc: An unholy alliance! Marking the feature film debut of one of Hollywood’s most influential and widely referenced auteur directors, Sam Peckinpah, The Deadly Companions centers on a redemptive journey to escort a funeral procession through dangerous Indian Territory. Featuring fine work from a top-notch cast that includes the inimitable Maureen O’Hara at the height of her illustrious career, Peckinpah’s first foray into film provides a promising glance into the energetic and violent nature of his iconic later works.

programme.title: Captain Scarlett
programme.desc: Captain Carlos Scarlett (Richard Greene) returns from the Napoleonic wars and finds that life in southern France has changed. The Duke of Corlais (Manolo Fabregas) has begun persecuting people, while a lovely princess is trying to escape an arranged marriage to an evil count (Eduardo Noriega). Scarlett will have his hands full restoring order! Also starring Leonora Amar and Nedrick Young, this independent production was filmed in Mexico by director Thomas Carr, who would go on to direct such classic television shows as The Adventures of Superman and Rawhide.

programme.title: The Deadly Game
programme.desc: An American on vacation in Spain gets mixed up with a smuggling ring.

programme.title: Kennel Murder Case (1933)
programme.desc: William Powell stars as detective Philo Vance in this suspenseful locked­room murder mystery. Along with a lot of head­scratching clues, there’s plenty of fun stuff about stuffy art collectors, plus... there’s a beautiful debutante trapped in a house of hate...A glamorous stage star keeping a tryst with a "dead" man...A corpse walking upstairs to commit suicide...And a wounded dog that knows the answer to the most inexplicable mystery ever tackled by the most captivating sleuth since Sherlock Holmes! Oscar winning Director Michael Curtiz (Casablanca) spins a tale that is absolutely guess­-proof!

programme.title: White Zombie (Friday Fright)
programme.desc: Watch Bela Lugosi use his special zombie grip to make beautiful women submit to his every desire! In this low budget screamer, a couple honeymooning in Haiti run afoul of a diabolical voodoo master. They’re soon wishing they’d gone to Cancun! This Pre-­Code horror classic is considered to be the first feature length zombie movie, and features great atmospheric direction by Victor Halperin. The film’s unsung hero was set designer Ralph Berger, who exploited sets of previous Universal Studios films, including bits from Dracula, The Hunchback of Notre Dame, and Frankenstein. Whatever you do, DON’T LOOK INTO LUGOSI’S EYES!

programme.title: Elvira's Movie Macabre: Maneater Of Hydra
programme.desc: Elvira presents the 1967 Horror film Maneater of Hydra.

programme.title: Last Man on Earth
programme.desc: Vincent Price plays a doctor who must try to single-handedly save the earth when a plague causes the rest of the human race to turn into Vampire Zombies.

programme.title: The Disappearance of Flight 412
programme.desc: There's so much mystery surrounding the disappearance of Flight 412. And why so much secrecy from the military? Did it, as some suspect, have something to do with flying saucers? An all-star cast headlines this weird drama, including Glenn Ford, Bradford Dilllman, and David Soul. Emmy winning director Jud Taylor was known for his TV production of The Old Man and The Sea, and several episodes of Law & Order: Special Victims Unit.

programme.title: Last Woman on Earth
programme.desc: When a woman and her husband resurface from a scuba dive in Puerto Rico, they conclude that an interruption of oxygen has killed off the rest of the human race.

programme.title: Lady Frankenstein
programme.desc: When Dr. Frankenstein is killed by his own creation, his daughter and his lab assistant, Marshall, continue his work. Together, they attempt to create a monster even greater than the one that killed Dr. Frankenstein. (Color)

programme.title: History of Flight
programme.desc: This 1953 documentary was used by United Aircraft to celebrate 50 years of flight. The film explores the first flight by the Wright Brothers in 1903 all the way up to 1953, featuring interviews and footage from pioneers like Frank Long, Igor Sikorsky, Glen Martin, Alan Lockheed, Eddie Rickenbacker, and more!

programme.title: The Trail Beyond (1934)
programme.desc: Rod Drew (John Wayne) is in search of a missing miner and his daughter in this Lone Star Picture. Along the way, Drew rescues his pal Wabbi (Noah Beery Jr.) from card cheats who have framed him for murder. You'll find plenty of action and suspense in this vintage horse opera, originally distributed by the kings of the B western, Monogram Pictures!

programme.title: Brothers of the West
programme.desc: Tom Tyler plays Tom Wade, a range detective whose brother has been accused of robbery and murder. Wade has only one clue to prove his brother’s innocence: a set of unusual tire tracks.

programme.title: “E for Efficiency”
programme.desc: Short Industrial Training film produced by Jam Handy.

programme.title: “The Velvet Glove”
programme.desc: Short Industrial Training film produced by Jam Handy.

programme.title: The Mummy Strikes
programme.desc: Superman must battle dangerous mummies while investigating an egyptologist's mysterious death.

programme.title: Me Musical Nephews
programme.desc: Popeye has a hard time putting his musical nephews to bed.

programme.title: The Lunar Luger
programme.desc: Dr. Destructo tests out his lates weapon, the Lunar Luger.

programme.title: Operation Moon Beam
programme.desc: Clutch enters into a rocket race to the moon.

programme.title: Woos Whoopee
programme.desc: After a fun night out at the Whoopee Club, Felix is followed home by figments of his drunken imagination.

programme.title: Song of the Birds
programme.desc: When a little boy shoots a baby bird with an air rifle, he soon learns the error in his ways when all the other birds go into mourning.

programme.title: Chaplin's Art of Comedy
programme.desc: An anthology consisting of excerpts from several of Chaplin's short films made for the Essanay Company, including The Tramp, Shanghaied, In the Park and The Bank.

programme.title: Raiders of Old California
programme.desc: The end of the Mexican-American War finds a brazen U.S. Calvary captain and his men taking over a Spanish land grant. Albert C. Gannaway (The Badge of Marshall Brennan) directs an all-star cast including Jim Davis (Jock Ewing of Dallas), Arleen Whelan (Young Mr. Lincoln) and Lee Van Cleef (The Good, The Bad, and the Ugly). Also, look for appearances by legendary country & western stars Marty Robbins and Faron Young.

programme.title: Day of Triumph
programme.desc: The last days of Jesus Christ's life on earth recounted. The story is not seen through the eyes of Christ, but looking through the eyes of two of his apostles, Andrew and Zadok.

programme.title: The Second Woman (1950)
programme.desc: James V. Kern went on to direct some of the top television shows of the 1950s and ‘60s, but not before directing this taught suspense tale. In the tradition of Hitchcock classics like Spellbound and Rebecca, this movie centers around a woman (Betsy Drake) who finds herself involved with a mysterious man (Robert Young) who may or may not be in grave danger. Filmed in Carmel­-by-­the-Sea and Monterey CA, with cinematography by two­time Oscar winner Hal Mohr (The Phantom of the Opera, A Midsummer Night’s Dream), this is a lush piece of forgotten cinema begging to be rediscovered...

programme.title: The Thief of Bagdad
programme.desc: Flying carpets! Giant apes! Underwater kingdoms! And a whole lot more! Douglas Fairbanks heads the cast of this riveting adventure from the silent movie era. Fairbanks, who also produced the feature and contributed to the story, plays the famous thief who battles a Mongol leader for the love of a beautiful princess. In its day, this was the extravaganza of the year, and is still regarded as one of the great fantasy films of all time. Attention movie buffs: look for a young Anna May Wong as a Mongol slave girl!

programme.title: MST3K: The Incredibly Strange Creatures Who Stopped Living And Became Mixed-Up Zombies
programme.desc: Joel and the robots sit through The Incredibly Strange Creatures Who Stopped Living And Became Mixed-Up Zombies. A film from 1964 which follows a group of beatniks at a mysterious seaside carnival.

programme.title: Sky High Lee & Rudy Kay vs. Lisowski & Sheik of Araby
programme.desc: Sky High Lee and Rudy Kay face off against Lisowski and the Sheik of Araby.

programme.title: Ben
programme.desc: A lonely little boy befriends a rat named Ben. Being the leader of a rat colony, Ben uses the colony to seek vengeance against those who harm the boy.

programme.title: Hollow Triumph (1948)
programme.desc: John Muller (Paul Henried), a career criminal on the run after a botched casino robbery, finds the ultimate hideout by taking on another man's identity. Produced by Henried and directed by low budget genius Steve Sekely ("Blonde Savage," "Revenge of the Zombies") the movie's fine cast includes Joan Bennett, Eduard Franz, and a very young Jack Webb. Noted cinematographer John Alton shoots in the same shimmering style that he brought to such films as "He Walked By Night" and "The Big Combo," giving "Hollow Triumph" enough stark atmosphere to match any of the great noir films.

programme.title: Night of the Living Dead (1968)
programme.desc: "Night of the Living Dead" opens with chaos - the brains of the recently deceased have become mysteriously reanimated, causing the dead to rise and feed on human flesh. While visiting their father's grave, Barbra (Judith O'Dea) and her brother Johnny (Russell Streiner) are attacked by a strange shuffling man. Barbra runs into a farmhouse where she encounters Ben (Duane Jones), and they must find a way to save themselves from the horde of zombies. George Romero's "Night of the Living Dead" is hailed as one of the most influential horror films of all time - inspirational, thought provoking, and most importantly, terrifying!

programme.title: Track of the Moon Beast
programme.desc: Paul Carlson has a horrible problem. A fragment from a meteorite has lodged in his skull; when the moon is full the fragment causes him to transform into a murderous beast. Screenwriters Bill Finger (best known for his work on the Batman comic book) and Charles Sinclair (The Green Slime) conjure a tale that includes everything from Native American legends to NASA brain surgeons.

programme.title: Mind Over Murder
programme.desc: When a young woman suffers a series of nightmares involving a bald man, a government agent seeks to uncover the truth when a plane crash appears to involve the man in the woman's dreams.

programme.title: The Monster from the Ocean Floor
programme.desc: Julie, an American on vacation in Mexico, spots a giant, one-eyed amoeba rising from the ocean, but when she tries to tell the authorities, no one believes her. She finally teams up with a marine biologist in an attempt to destroy it.

programme.title: The Adventurer
programme.desc: After escaping prison, the Little Tramp saves a girl and her mother from nearly drowning, and then creates havoc at a swanky party.

programme.title: Irish Luck
programme.desc: Frankie Darro stars as hotel bellhop Buzzy O'Brien in this manic comedy from Monogram Pictures. When a guest is found murdered, the police blame Kitty Monahan (Sheila Darcy), but Buzzy helps her escape and hides her at his mother's house. The cast also includes Dick Purcell, Mantan Moreland, and James Flavin, but it's all Frankie Darro's show as the well-meaning Buzzy. Will the luck of the Irish help him solve the murder? That's what this nervy, snoopy, reckless bellhop is counting on!

programme.title: West of the Divide (1934)
programme.desc: John Wayne stars as Ted Hayden, a tough hombre who goes undercover to join a gang led by a heartless fiend known only as "Mr. Gentry" (Lloyd Whitlock). Gentry is out to take over a ranch belonging to one of Hayden's friends, but as Hayden finds out, Gentry has a lot more than that up his sleeve. You'll have to watch this two-fisted Western to find out the rest!

programme.title: Dean Martin's Red Hot Scandals Of 1926

This colorful, comical film was directed by Victor Schertzinger ("The Road to Zanzibar," "The Road to Singapore") who also wrote the movie’s many songs. The movie also features a superb supporting cast which includes William Frawley ("I Love Lucy"), and Dwight Fry ("Dracula").

programme.title: Sitting on the Moon (1936)
programme.desc: In a misguided and selfish attempt to rekindle the career of the lovely fading movie star Polly, songwriter Danny promptly ends his long standing partnership with his lyricist, Mike. Not content to take the injustice lying down, the dejected Mike sends in a blonde seductress to try and break up Polly and the smitten Danny. With three-time Oscar nominee Ralph Staub taking the reins behind the camera, the rousing, crowd-pleasing Sitting on the Moon is a roaring good time for the whole family. Featuring typically solid turns from B-movie musical crooner Roger Pryor (Belle of the Nineties) and Broadway mainstay Pert Kelton (The Music Man), performing the film's six original musical numbers with gusto to spare.

programme.title: I'm From Arkansas (1944)

The event attracts many tourists and real life country musicians to Pitchfork, including Mary Ford, Merle Travis, Jimmy Wakely, and countless others. Starring as Farmer Jenkins is Slim Summerville, a former Keystone Cop who became one of Hollywood's most reliable journeyman, appearing in everything from Charlie Chan and Shirley Temple movies, to the classic All Quiet on the Western Front.

After a passionate moment in the ball pit, Billie and Zara both begin to question what they want. But the playland is soon to be closed - and Billie’s anxiety can only handle so much. programme.title: The Millennial Experience
programme.desc: The Millennial Experience is one part dance-for-film and one part documentary. The film explores cultural appropriation vs appreciation, LGBTQIA+ culture, feminism and how these topics impact the Millennial generation. The dance sequences in the film are adapted from director Alex Crozier's stage production MILLENNIALS which focuses on the aforementioned themes. Fourteen on-camera interviews that expound on the main topics were conducted with people of various ages, ethnicities, sexual orientations, and genders . The Millennial Experience seeks to uplift the voices of women, LGBTQIA+, and BIPOC communities in an effort to create a more equitable and just world.

programme.title: Culture Q
programme.desc: Culture Q is the world’s first weekly queer-centric news series brought to you by the leading global queer streaming network, Revry. This innovative, weekly news series creatively features entertainment, pop culture, lifestyle and political news with wit and insightfully nuanced perspectives. Emphasizing the queer millieu, Culture Q stands to be the leading, weekly forum for boundary-pushing discussions and commentary. Hosted by digital news influencer pioneers, Shira Lazar and Andy Lalwani of the highly successful What’s Trending, Culture Q will feature an ever-changing cavalcade of guests who help capture that X-factor which defines queer culture.

programme.title: The Billionaire

The film is a throwback to Classic Hollywood films, stylistically and tonally.

programme.title: Out On Stage
programme.desc: Out On Stage is THE absolutely hilarious and one-of-a-kind, originally produced comedy hosted by Zach Noe Towers! See OUT Magazine's "1 of the 10 comedians to watch in 2018," the comedian that Sarah Silverman calls, "So, SO, SO Funny" and 17 other top-rated Gay and Lesbian stand-up comedians discuss taboo subjects as only they can!

programme.title: Queens & Cowboys
programme.desc: Roping and riding across North America, the International Gay Rodeo Association's courageous cowboys and cowgirls brave challenges both in and out of the arena on their quest to qualify for the World Finals. Along the way, they’ll bust every stereotype in the book. The film tells the story of five members of the IGRA. From Wade Earp, a descendant of cowboy legend Wyatt Earp and one of the best competitors on the circuit, to Char Duran, a female bull rider who’s never won a buckle but seems determined to die trying, “QUEENS & COWBOYS” weaves the stories of its protagonists over the course of an entire rabble-rousing year. An unprecedented look at the strength it takes to be gay in the rural west, this film explores the many struggles threatening the IGRA and the gay community at large, how far society has come on the subject of gay equality, and how far we still have to go.

programme.title: The Dead Mothers Club
programme.desc: The (Dead Mothers) Club tells the story of three women- a Southern artist redefining herself through her art; a high school senior struggling to gain independence; and a Brazilian living in NY, navigating first-time motherhood – all of whom lost their mothers during adolescence. The film reveals how coming of age without their mothers has and continues to play a role in their lives. Structured around a series of ‘dialogues’ featuring Rosie O’Donnell, Molly Shannon and Jane Fonda that focus on various themes threading their stories together, these ruminations allow for heart-breaking and at times humorous insight into how ultimately one’s past can dictate their future. From the cyclical nature of grief to their own mortality, the women of The Club provoke thoughts surrounding the innate, complicated nature of the mother/daughter relationship, even in its absence.

programme.title: The Guys Next Door
programme.desc: Who, among us, can say that we come from a “normal” family? The Guys Next Door, a feature length documentary, offers an alternative to the traditional ideas of what constitute the nuclear American family. Meet Erik and Sandro, a gay couple with two daughters birthed by their friend Rachel with donor eggs. In her 40s, Rachel is married to Tony and they have three biological children of their own. Rachel and Tony, a seemingly traditional married couple, live in the suburbs of Massachusetts with their children. Inspired by a TV program about the difficulties and costs associated with gay couples having children, Rachel, age 41, volunteers to be a surrogate – not once, but twice within two years – for Erik, her good friend from college, and his husband Sandro, an Italian émigré. This film begins when Rachel is eight months pregnant with Erik and Sandro’s second daughter, Eleonora. What compels a woman in her forties with three children of her own to carry children for friends? What is the reaction of her husband and children? And, how will Erik and Sandro handle the challenges of parenting two girls in a world that still emphasizes the importance of maternal instinct? The issues raised in this film - gay marriage and parenting, surrogacy as a path for gays and lesbians to have children, and the extension and redefinition of what it means to be “an American family" - remain relevant as our country is a cultural battleground during the divisive 2016 presidential election. The Guys Next Door is a powerful antidote to the negative backlash and hateful rhetoric aimed at same sex families. In the words of the esteemed documentary filmmaker Ross McElwee (Sherman’s March), “with nuance, verve and humor, this film goes well beyond issues of surrogacy and gay parenthood and explores the humanity that connects us all."

programme.title: Becoming Queen

programme.title: Memories Of A Penitent Heart
programme.desc: Combining a wealth of recently discovered home movies, video, and written documents with artfully shot contemporary interviews and vérité footage, Memories Of A Penitent Heart is a documentary that cracks open a Pandora’s box of unresolved family drama. Originating from filmmaker Cecilia Aldarondo’s suspicion that there was something ugly in her family’s past, the film charts her excavation of the buried family conflict around her uncle Miguel’s death, and her search for Miguel’s partner Robert a generation later. After two years of dead ends, Robert turns up: but he’s not the same man. He’s reinvented himself as Father Aquin, a Franciscan monk with twenty-five years of pent-up grief and bitterness. For the first time, a member of Miguel’s family wants to hear Aquin’s side of the story—but is it too little, too late? ​A story about the mistakes of the past and the second chances of the present, Memories Of A Penitent Heart is a cautionary tale about the unresolved conflicts wrought by AIDS, and a nuanced exploration of how faith is used and abused in times of crisis.

programme.title: Unlikely Family
programme.desc: Follow this Unlikely Family as it challenges the archaic ideology that being openly gay - and Christian - is incompatible.

programme.title: The Walk-In Closet
programme.desc: S1 E1-4 | Dana delivers a big package. Sterling receives some very, very scary news./Sterling is very, very sad and drunk; Billie does a Drew Barrymore impression. They come up with a plan!/ It's Billie's straight brother Dom's birthday!/It's time for the first real test! Billie and Sterling meet Ms. Hutchcroft, the immigration official.

programme.title: The Walk-In Closet
programme.desc: S1 E5-8 | Billie goes to "work" at the "comedy" club./Sterling and Billie keep up the super, super good work of passing as straight at the local gym. Dana makes another delivery./Ms. Hutchcroft makes a home visit./Billie and Sterling come to a tough realization.

programme.title: Words
programme.desc: "Words" explores how people navigate gender & identity in the open & evolving landscape of NYC. Featuring exclusive interviews from a variety of artists, activists, icons & innovators. Powerful tribute to the language we use to shape our identities.

programme.title: Gay Mean Girls
programme.desc: S1 E3-4 | Lucy visits the Gay Straight Alliance to gain support for Gay Prom Royalty. She shares some personal secrets to old and new friends. Anita’s throwing a party and a surprise promposal! Lucy has social anxiety about it.

programme.title: The QueerX Awards
programme.desc: The circus is in town and just in time for National Coming Out Day! Welcome to the 2021 QueerX Awards brought to you by Lexus. Join us as hosts, Drew Droege and Raneir Pollard, take us on a carnival tour of LGBTQ music, films, and icons! Featuring appearances by Bowen Yang, Michaela Jaé Rodriguez, Patton Oswalt, Dwyane Wade, Erica Wheeler, and Elvira, Mistress of the Dark, Cassandra Peterson. And don’t miss the special performances by Chanel and the Circus, Mila Jam, and Alsace Carcione.

programme.title: Culture Q
programme.desc: Culture Q is the world’s first weekly queer-centric news series brought to you by the leading global queer streaming network, Revry. This innovative, weekly news series creatively features entertainment, pop culture, lifestyle and political news with wit and insightfully nuanced perspectives. Emphasizing the queer millieu, Culture Q stands to be the leading, weekly forum for boundary-pushing discussions and commentary. Hosted by digital news influencer pioneers, Shira Lazar and Andy Lalwani of the highly successful What’s Trending, Culture Q will feature an ever-changing cavalcade of guests who help capture that X-factor which defines queer culture.

programme.title: Rave Train
programme.desc: Rave Train is a video series that features live EDM DJ and Artist performances with a diverse range of dancers from the Rave culture. SOUL TRAIN meets EDM; Rave Train brings movement to sound with the latest dance styles with today’s upcoming Electronic Music artists.

programme.title: No Time For Quiet
programme.desc: Struggling to establish a sense of belonging and identity, a group of teenagers find their voice through a unique rock 'n' roll community.

programme.title: Barbelle
programme.desc: S1 E7-10 | Alice and Veronica head to the studio to work on the new album. After Karen informs Alice that Lulu will no longer be working on the new album, Alice realizes this might be the end of her and Lulu's relationship. Veronica attempts to win back Alice by writing the perfect song. Her writer's block leads to a downward spiral of shoplifting and booze only hours before she is set to accompany Brooklyn to prom. Alice confronts Veronica about her poor choices. Veronica wakes up to find The Ghost of Girlfriend's Past waiting to take her on a Dickensian journey through her past. Alice accompanies Brooklyn to her prom in Veronica's stead. Lulu shows up to the prom unannounced, as does another surprise guest.↵

programme.title: Barbelle
programme.desc: S2 E1-2 | Alice and Veronica try to keep their rekindled romance under wraps. Lulu and her bandmates invite Alice out for a night on the town. At a press conference for their upcoming tour, Richard leaks a secret about Veronica to the media.

programme.title: Cameron Esposito: Marriage Material
programme.desc: In her first special, the purveyor of fine jokes, Cameron Esposito, has some harsh truths for you. From the secrets of a women's locker room to her stance on gun control, she gets real. And, we wouldn't have it any other way. She's Marriage Material.

programme.title: Shutter Rush: City of Abandonment
programme.desc: Three photographers set out to explore the abandoned city of Gary, Indiana. Once on the FBI's most dangerous place to live. Now just a city of ruins.

programme.title: I'm From Driftwood
programme.desc: Laverne Cox: I'm From Mobile/New Teacher Encounters Homophobia In Second Week/Coming Out Again To Grandma With Alzheimer's/Gender Bending And Runway Walking In A McDonald's Parking Lot/Homeless, Transgender And Finding Her Way/Trans Woman Sacrifices Everything To Finally Be Herself/Transgender High School Student Encounters Cyberbullying/A Broken Down Car, Matching Tattoos, And A Love Story/Agender Person Goes From Being Bullied In The Newark Projects To Gracing The Cover of French Vogue/ Alan Cumming: True Bisexual Stories S1 E1-10 | Laverne Cox remembers the bullying she experienced as a child, and how it's similar to the transphobia she experiences as an adult. Alexa moved from New York City to small-town Jackson, Mississippi, to teach at an under-priveleged school. After only two weeks in, Alexa had to challenge homophobia in the hallway, and had some surprising success. Megan's grandma was supportive and excited when she found out Megan was a lesbian. But after showing signs of Alzheimer's, Megan's grandma forgot and kept asking her if she was seeing any special boy. Megan received a special phone call from her grandma, though, that she'll remember forever. Jacob Tobia, activist for genderqueer, gender non-conforming, and transgender issues, bought a single pair of black pumps while organizing a Gender Nonconforming Day for their high school, a small act that would change the course of their life. After being kicked out of her home at 17, Angela Louis struggled with homelessness, abusive relationships, sex work, and depression, all while transitioning, but nothing could stop her from finding her own path and earning her diploma. Mila Jam had it all, or so she thought. Her drag persona, Britney Houston, had a massive YouTube following and she performed on a hit TV show in London. But she gave it all up so that she could finally live her truth as a woman and as herself. Olivia Page was brave enough to transition in high school. Unfortunately, a classmate decided to cyberbully her on Facebook. Olivia also had the support and kindness of a teacher who helped her through high school. A wild series of events led Sam to meeting the love of her life. Andre J. wants to tell you one thing: Love Yourself. That's how Andre went from being bullied in the projects to appearing on the cover of French Vogue. Alan Cumming remembers when he first felt an attraction to guys and how he came out to American media in a big way. - Externals

programme.title: Amplify Voices
programme.desc: S1 E10 | A healing deep-dive conversation among two brave men discussing navigating sexual orientation, norms, family and societal pressures and sexual assault.

programme.title: Room To Grow
programme.desc: S1 E2 | Cody (Elton Cray) is a professional musician & rapper. We did an initial interview with him in his home, then visited with him almost 10 months later at one of his shows. An interesting and passionate man who speaks his mind, Cody's music is about his struggles with himself and others around him who have been indifferent to how he identifies.

programme.title: Room To Grow
programme.desc: S1 E3 | Miles and Matthias have an adorable father/son relationship. They’ve seen some hard times, but it’s brought them closer together. Miles talks about what it was like for him to go through a divorce as an LGBTQ+ teenager.

programme.title: For My Wife
programme.desc: A feature documentary chronicling the making of an activist. After the tragic death of her wife, Charlene Strong was thrust into the spotlight becoming a powerful voice ;for the equal rights of same-sex couples and their families.

programme.title: RABBIT WOMAN

programme.title: Meet Clean Green Certified Founder Chris Van Hook
programme.desc: Certification for sustainable, naturally-grown agriculture, Clean Green Certified is the closest to “Organic” that the cannabiz can get. We're honored to welcome founder Chris Van Hook. Together, we explore the value of certification for industry operators, consumers and the planet. Chris offers tips and tricks that you can put to use in your own garden. Dig in! Founded in 2004, Swami Select has had the pleasure of being Clean Green Certified since 2011.

programme.title: Meet the International Canna Farmer's Association Chair, Kristin Nevedal
programme.desc: We're honored to welcome to today's show, Kristin Nevedal, International Cannabis Farmer's Association Chair. The International Cannabis Farmer’s Association strives to empower traditional Cannabis farmers through education, research and advocacy. Their programs raise public awareness about the benefits of traditionally farmed Cannabis and provide educational resources for farmers, regulators, industry and consumers. They advocate for the development of responsible regulations in CA, which are seen as crucially important due to the state’s significance to national and international policy development. They will promote public policy that ensures an equal share of licenses are issued to traditional sun grown Cannabis farmers. They conduct research to quantify the ecological superiority of traditionally farmed Cannabis as well as gathering data necessary to establish internationally recognized appellations of origin. They create a dynamic and creative consumer direct educational campaign that highlights the quality and ecological superiority of traditionally farmed sun grown Cannabis.

programme.title: What's It Like to Judge The Emerald Cup - Go Backstage with Swami Select
programme.desc: Founded in 2003, Northern California’s Emerald Cup advances the concept of sustainable, outdoor farming of medical cannabis. Longtime advocates of the spiritually and physically healing potential of regeneratively-grown cannabis, Swami Select founders Nikki Lastreto and Swami Chaitanya have judged The Emerald Cup’s flower competition since the event began. As the largest, organic, outdoor, medicinal cannabis competition in the world, The Cup advances our movement by cross-pollinating cultivators, patients and patrons with scientific and agriculture experts who work across industries. Now a global movement, the community celebration honors the year’s best, sun-grown, medicinal cannabis producers.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Actor & Comedian Aries Spear
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is actor comedian Aries Spears. From TV to film, actor Aries Spears spends some time with DL and Jasmine to talk about recent issues with Mike Epps and a social media post about black on black crime versus police racism against blacks.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Actor Miguel A. Nunez
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is actor Miguel Nunez. From TV to film, actor Miguel Nunez spends some time with DL and Jasmine to talk about his career, life as a black actor and discuss some of the issues of today.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Alonzo Bodden
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is standup comedian and former “Last Comic Standing” champion Alonzo Bodden. DL and Alonzo discuss the issues of the pandemic and working as entertainers. They also discuss politics, racism, and other issues in the black community.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Atty Ben Crump
programme.desc: DL Hughley Uncut on GFNTV. Guest on DL Uncut is Civil Rights Attorney Benjamin Crump. Attorney Crump is best known for taking on the toughest cases with national civil rights implications. From Trayvon Martin to Michael Brown, Crump continues to push the envelope for justice for those whose lives have been changed due an unfair legal system.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Charlamagne Tha God
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is one of the hosts on the nationally syndicated radio show The Breakfast Club – Charlamagne Tha God.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest David A. Arnold
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is stand-up comedian, writer and producer David Arnold. He has a special on Netflix called “Fat Ballerina”.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest DJ Doug E. Fresh
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Hughley Uncut is legendary DJ and Hip Hop pioneer Doug E. Fresh. Chris Spencer, the creator of the Real Husbands of Hollywood spends some time with DL and Jasmine to talk about his recent projects and working during a pandemic.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Erika Alexander
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is the brilliant actress from “The Cosby Show” and the 90’s hit series “Living Single” – Erika Alexander. Erika is a producer on the upcoming documentary “John Lewis: Good Trouble” which will release on July 3. DL, Jasmine, and Erika have a great discussion about the creating of “Living Single” and how the show “Friends” became a bigger hit after using the same concept. Erika gives great insight into racism in the entertainment industry.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Leonard Pitts
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is Pulitzer Prize Winner and columnist for the Miami Herald Leonard Pitts, Jr. Leonard Pitts has a progressive voice in journalism who dives deep into the racial and cultural issues of society.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Matt Barnes
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is former NBA star and 2017 NBA Champion Matt Barnes. Matt discusses his upbringing, thoughts on now legalized marijuana. Matt also gives his thoughts on George Floyd and the affects on our society.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Tamika Mallory
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is activist and the former chair of the Women’s March Tamika Mallory. Currently she is the co-founder of the social justice organization Until Freedom. DL, Jasmine, and Tamika share a deep discussion of the after effects of George Floyd’s murder by police, protests, and where civil unrest is headed in America.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Willy T Ribbs
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is former race car driver Willy T. Ribbs. Willy was the first African American to test a Formula One racing car and first African American to compete in the Indy 500. DL, Jasmine and Willy discuss the sport of auto racing, the lack of diversity, and the future of sport in the changing times of America.

programme.title: Ali in the Valley | Easy French Onion Soup
programme.desc: This Easy French Onion Soup is rich, comforting and so good with toasted cheesy bread for dipping! What better way to kick off Season 4 of Ali in the Valley than with a delicious decadent classic French Onion Soup. French Onion Soup is such a classic and SO easy to make! Onions are slowly caramelized until soft and sweet, simmered with beef broth, and just a touch of sugar. It’s topped with crispy croutons, loads of shredded gruyere cheese, and broiled into crispy, cheesy oblivion. So good!

programme.desc: The secret to cooking the perfect filet mignon is to combine pan searing with an oven finish. programme.title: Stepdads The Sketch- Ep 1
programme.desc: When infidelity claims the life of Joanne Bates, her children Lisa and Stevie are left in the custody of her fiancé Mike and his brother Jerry. Mike, a straight-laced, hardworking accountant; and Jerry, a wild, unstable, womanizer were both former foster children and together they provide a unique balance of parenting skills for young Lisa and Stevie. - Step Dads starring Ben Sloane (R.I.P.D, Alpha House), Morocco Omari (Empire, 21 Bridges, Homeland, Chicago Fire), Jorie Binion (Chicago P.D) Charles Dunlap (Chicago Fire, Empire), and Jay Davis (Not Another Black Movie, Choke On That: The Series, Not Another Zombie Movie) is a comedy about two polar opposite foster brothers raising two children using non-traditional parenting methods while shedding a satirical light on the importance of adoption. We poke fun at some of the mishaps which comes along with the shock of being a new parent, but ultimately, we hope to spread awareness on adoption, the importance of having fathers and father-figures in the lives of young people, and having a familial loving environment. The moral of our story is that “No family is perfect, but every child deserves to be loved unconditionally, and raised in a reliable, stable support system.”

programme.title: Europa
programme.desc: Discovering and exploring Jupiter's most promising moon, Europa. Europa was named after a Phoenician noblewoman who was abducted by Zeus after he had transformed himself into a bull. Rather fittingly, Zeus established Europa on the island of Crete as its queen, where he had several children with her, including Minos, the legendary king of Crete. In later ages, the continent of Europe would be named after Europa.

programme.title: Jupiter
programme.desc: Jupiter is the fifth planet from our Sun and is, by far, the largest planet in the solar system – more than twice as massive as all the other planets combined. Jupiter’s stripes and swirls are actually cold, windy clouds of ammonia and water, floating in an atmosphere of hydrogen and helium. Jupiter’s iconic Great Red Spot is a giant storm bigger than Earth that has raged for hundreds of years.

programme.title: Edinburgh and Scotland
programme.desc: Friendly and feisty, Scotland makes us feel right at home. In Edinburgh, we climb the ramparts of this city's famous castle, shop for kilts, visit mysterious Rosslyn Chapel and gasp on a ghost tour. Then we head to historic St. Andrew's to practice our swing on the world's most famous golf course.

programme.title: Barcelona and Costa Brava
programme.desc: A Mediterranean marvel, Barcelona simmers with beautiful beaches, medieval mazes, eye popping art and hypnotic architecture. From tapas bars, to surrealist art, to Modernist structures, we will feast on Barcelona's delights.

programme.title: Edmonton, Canada
programme.desc: In the second part of her tour of Alberta, Canada, you and Donna will discover fresh cuisine at the local farmer's market and explore some of the region’s crafts. You will also go snowshoeing and learn how to ski.

programme.title: S8E9 - Amsterdam
programme.desc: Uniquely entertaining Amsterdam shows off its Rembrandts and Van Goghs, rivers of bikes, and pot-filled coffeeshops — all under gabled facades leaning out over placid canals.

programme.title: Perth Western Australia
programme.desc: In Western Australia, Jason visits vineyards, goes on a food adventure for crayfishes, truffles, and finger limes, and visits a Brazilian food in Perth city.

programme.title: Traditional Tastes
programme.desc: Morocco (Cities): Tony is invited to experience the culinary heart and distinct walled medinas (districts) of the Moroccan city Fes.

programme.title: Savannah
programme.desc: We visit the old South and enjoy some sweet tea in Savannah. On this episode, we will stroll the city’s beautiful squares, as well as visit its civil war past at Old Fort Jackson. Then, we head up the stairs of the famous Tybee Island lighthouse and visit the Savannah Railroad museum.

programme.title: S7E4 - Florence: Heart of the Renaissance
programme.desc: In Florence, we'll revel in the genius of Michelangelo and Botticelli, climb the dome that kicked off the Renaissance, and cross the Arno to take in modern-day artisan life.

programme.title: The Cook Who Came in From the Cold
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony plays spy in Russia and sets off to locate the best blinis and borscht St. Petersburg has to offer.

programme.title: So Much Vodka, So Little Time
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony continues his mission with a tour of local working-class specialties. He tries his hand at ice-fishing, drinks a lot of vodka, feasts on Russian foods, eats smoked fish and ends the outing with a dip in the outdoor cold pool.

programme.title: Longyearbyen
programme.desc: Only 650 miles from the North Pole, there are three seasons in Longyearbyen: Polar summer, Northern Lights winter, and Sunny winter, and the elemental side of nature is a common factor in all decisions. The crystalline, light-lit hues of the land can remind one that true spirit shines from within.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Melbourne Victoria
programme.desc: Jason catches his own lunch at Buxton trout farm, visits a stone fruit orchard, learns how to make sausages at The Green Olive, and learns secrets of cooking from top Australian chef, Guy Grossi.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: The New China
programme.desc: China is a young, vibrant culture that is making things happen in the world that will affect everyone. This "inside look" at China by Geographic Travel filmmaker Dale Johnson explores China's explosive double-digit growth that has made it among the world's leading economies, with extra potential.

programme.title: Tarpan: Repainting an Ancient Picture
programme.desc: The Tarpan roamed in wild herds across Europe for millennia, yet the breed became extinct in the 19th century. Today, international teams have introduced a herd of genetically bred, modern Tarpan to remote mountains of Eastern Europe where they hope the horses can find their wild spirits again.

programme.title: Mad Tony: The Food Warrior
programme.desc: Tony embarks on a pilgrimage to Sydney, Australia so he may indulge in a meal made by one of the world's best chefs - Tetsuya Wakuda.

programme.title: Down Under: The Wild West of Cooking
programme.desc: Melbourne, Australia boasts hard-living, good-natured, and eccentric lovers of food - Tony's kind of people. In search of the outlaws of food, Tony explores a pasteurization-free cheese factory, and an old-world cured jamon workshop.

programme.title: Singapore: New York in Twenty Years
programme.desc: Tony sets out to find the real Singapore, with its multicultural restaurants and food markets. He samples prescription food dishes, explores the Geyland Serai Market, and rides the clean and efficient local subway.

programme.title: Taste of Japan: Kyushu
programme.desc: Explore the island of Kyushu with it's dramatic landscape and hot sands, and discover the essence of Japanese cuisine with Daisuke Utagawa and Rudy Maxa.

programme.title: Taste of Japan: Tokyo
programme.desc: Rudy Maxa and Daisuke Utagawa take us to the heart of Japan in Tokyo where culinary geniuses strive for perfection as they prepare everything from sushi to the wasabi.

programme.title: Taste of Japan: Hokkaido
programme.desc: Rudy Maxa and Daisuke Utagawa take you to Japan's northern frontier Hokkaido. The hot spring capital of Japan with its many volcanoes, Hokkaido also boosts some of the world greatest ramen, ramen noodles, and legendary whiskey.

programme.title: Hong Kong, Part 1
programme.desc: Host Rudy Maxa and Washington, D.C. restaurateur and chef Daisuke Utagawa enthusiastically eat their way through Hong Kong, from cheap but authentic, hole-in-the-wall Chinese restaurants to Michelin-starred palaces. Along the way they illustrate the excitement and energy that defines Hong Kong.

programme.title: Hong Kong, Part 2
programme.desc: Dramatic photography by renowned shooters Karel Bauer and Joe Pontecorvo bring Hong Kong into viewers' homes as never before. Stray from the iconic photo of Hong Kong as a wall of skyscrapers against Victoria Peak with the city's harbor in a foreground and visits the other side of the island.

programme.title: Bangkok
programme.desc: Washington, DC, restaurateur Daisuke Utagawa and travel journalist Rudy Max deliver viewers directly to Bangkok’s sprawling city temples, its huge flower market, its vibrant klongs (canals), and to its most interesting cuisine, all of which made Bangkok the world’s most-visited city by travelers.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Explore Las Vegas’ lesser known past. We visit the National Atomic Testing museum to learn about how the desert outside of Vegas was used for testing America’s secret nuclear weapons. We also visit the Mormon Fort, the first permanent non-native settlement in the area, as well as the Neon Museum.

programme.title: Wild National Parks
programme.desc: From grizzly bears of Katmai National Park in Alaska to rattlesnakes of Montezuma's Castle in Arizona, answer the call of America's wildest national parks. By land, sea, and sky, get up close to creatures of all shapes and sizes. Dedicated park workers reveal what it takes to nurture nature.

programme.title: The Mohawk Trail Across New England
programme.desc: The Mohawk Trail is deeply embedded in the history of America. For many years it served as a main trade route for indigenous tribes. As European settlement expanded, the Mohawk Trail began to change as the country itself changed. Tap into one of America’s richest springs of historical significance.

programme.title: The Iron Curtain Trail
programme.desc: For almost half a century, Europe was demonstrably divided into East and West by the "Iron Curtain,” an imaginary, yet strongly re-enforced, barrier separating Europe that stretched between the Barents and Black Seas. For 40 years, the Iron Curtain was a potent symbol of division between people.

programme.title: S8E9 - Amsterdam
programme.desc: Uniquely entertaining Amsterdam shows off its Rembrandts and Van Goghs, rivers of bikes, and pot-filled coffeeshops — all under gabled facades leaning out over placid canals.

programme.title: Elements of a Great Bar
programme.desc: Join Tony on his quest to characterize the perfect bar in New York City. Discover the importance of a maniacal bartender, the proper chemical makeup of drinks, the joys of seedy dive-bars, and the need for late-night snacks.

programme.title: Mad Tony: The Food Warrior
programme.desc: Tony embarks on a pilgrimage to Sydney, Australia so he may indulge in a meal made by one of the world's best chefs - Tetsuya Wakuda.

programme.title: Salt Lake City
programme.desc: Westward ho! We settle in Salt Lake City, where we learn about Brigham Young's settlement of the Utah territory and his monument at This is the Place Park. Then we dig in the dirt to find hundreds of perfectly preserved dinosaurs at the Utah Natural History museum.

programme.title: Albany/Saratoga Springs
programme.desc: Take the Albany capital tour and learn about five former N.Y. governors who became U.S. Presidents. Board the U.S.S. Slater and see how America defended its fleet against German U-boats in World War II. Then, sample the mineral water in Saratoga Springs and bet the farm at the thoroughbred raceway.

programme.title: Egypt - Water And Sand
programme.desc: Siwa is an island-oasis of fire-torched skies in the middle of the Egyptian desert where The Great Sand Sea comes to rest at the foot of an oasis of date palms. Bordered by two lakes of turquoise blue, travelers find themselves at an oasis that is authentically North African.

programme.title: Dominican Republic - Caribbean Treasure
programme.desc: Explore the lesser-known jungles, mountains, and lakes of the Dominican Republic, catch a glimpse of the fascinating history of the Tainos Indians, and listen to the electrifying steps and sounds of merengue dance and salsa music on this Caribbean treasure.

programme.title: From Guatemala to the Congo
programme.desc: Stewardship of the land is a central part of the human condition. Unfortunately, in some cases, so is greed. Meet people from California, Congo, India, Australia, Guatemala, and Slovenia whose spirit matches their intent to live healthily.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: France's Normandy
programme.desc: From a dramatic coast to rural pastures, this sweet section of France abounds with apple orchards, enchanting villages, stunning abbeys, and sparkling seaports. We base in the lovely seaside town Honfleur. At Giverny, and in the museums in Rouen and Honfleur, we discover the birth of Impressionism.

programme.title: Medieval Europe
programme.desc: The medieval world is one of the big draws of European Travel. Moody ruins, "tippy" towers, cobbled streets, sparkling mosaics, monasteries, castles, and cathedrals form the core of many a tourist's dreams. In this episode, we make sense out of a fascinating 1,000 years of history.

programme.title: Santa Barbara, California
programme.desc: Follow Donna to Santa Barbara, California, the “American Rivera,” and learn how to surf. Also, stay in an award-winning resort, and enjoy a dinner at restaurant that only uses organic local ingredients.

programme.title: S8E8 - Italy's Verona, Padova, and Ravenna
programme.desc: We'll visit three great cities in the shadow of Venice: Padova (Padua), with its university life and famed basilica; Verona and its Roman ruins; and Ravenna, for its shimmering mosaics.

programme.title: Adelaide South Australia
programme.desc: Jason visits Australia’s oldest winery in Adelaide and has a memorable dining experience in one of Australia’s top dining experiences, Restaurant Orana. For some sightseeing, he rides a bike through the sensational Barossa Valley.

programme.title: The Cook Who Came in From the Cold
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony plays spy in Russia and sets off to locate the best blinis and borscht St. Petersburg has to offer.

programme.title: St. Augustine
programme.desc: First, we will take a sip from the distinctively tasting Fountain of Youth. Then we will touch the coquina walls of the undefeated Castillo San Marcos. Next, separate pirate truth from pirate myth at the appropriately named, Pirate Museum, and cure what ails us at the oldest General Store.

programme.title: S7E5 - Florentine Delights and on exciting Tuscan Side Trips
programme.desc: We enjoy Renaissance art in Florence, the city that propelled Europe out of the Middle Ages. Then we visit two cultural capitals in their own right: Pisa, where we’ll marvel at a tipsy tower; and Lucca, where we’ll celebrate Puccini.

programme.title: Los Angeles, My Own Heart of Darkness
programme.desc: Los Angeles, CA: New York chef, Anthony Bourdain, descends into the culinary underbelly of his metropolitan nemesis, Los Angeles, where he experiences the trials of celebrity fame and the joys of West Coast cuisine.

programme.title: The French Laundry Experience
programme.desc: Napa, CA: Marooned in San Francisco, Tony tastes local shellfish and durian ice cream before embarking on a pilgrimage to experience the genius of Thomas Keller, chef and owner of The French Laundry.

programme.title: La Paz
programme.desc: Amid the dizzying heights of the Andes Mountains sits Laz Paz, Bolivia. The Mirandas, the friendly family Alexandra will be staying with, introduces her to elements of Bolivian culture that they keep close to their hearts. Also, meet famous Bolivian chola Glenda Yanez.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Tamales and Iguana, Oaxacan Style
programme.desc: Oaxaca, Mexico: Chef Tony Bourdain explores the exotic and colorful indigenous zone of Mexico's Oaxaca region where he tastes toasted grasshoppers and other delicacies. His adventure ends with mariachi music and, of course, lots of tequila.

programme.title: Cod Crazy
programme.desc: Portugal: Portuguese cuisine holds a dear place in Tony's culinary heart. Tony travels to Porto, home of the famous Port wine, where he is immediately exposed to the codfish and the almost mythical place it holds in Portuguese cuisine and culture.

programme.title: San Francisco
programme.desc: Stroll down Grant Street with Laura into the heart of America's largest Chinatown. Bike, drive, or walk across the Golden Gate Bridge, the city's most recognizable landmark. Finally, Fisherman's Wharf offers day trips all wrapped into one fun location.

programme.title: Versailles
programme.desc: Enter 12 miles of enclosing walls, 26 acres of roof, and over 2,000 windows and experience the royal Palace of Versailles. If you are looking for some good ole' fun, then you will enjoy Parc Asterix. Place Vendome is the top spot for high-end merchandise.

programme.title: Gold Coast Australia
programme.desc: If you like sun, surf, sand, and a laid-back lifestyle then join Laura on Australia's Gold Coast. Travel into the thick of the Queensland Rainforest, and visit the home of the largest collection of Australian native animals in the Carrumbin Wildlife Sanctuary.

programme.title: Sicily
programme.desc: Begin on the east coast in Taormina. Laura then takes us to some of Sicily's highlight cities, Palermo and Randazzo. How about a visit to Agrigento, or to the divinely inspired Cathedral Monreale? We will also visit Mt. Etna, an active volcano.

programme.title: Venice
programme.desc: Begin with a tour down the Grand Canal, "the finest street in the world." Next, the pedestrian streets around the Rialto Bridge are lined with shops, and St. Mark's Basilica is one of the oldest and most beautiful Byzantine cathedrals in all of Europe.

programme.title: Oahu, Hawaii
programme.desc: Have a blast with Laura on this Hawaiian voyage as you explore sensational surf and beaches, unique Hawaiian culture and food, and climb volcanic mountains. Join Laura as she visits historic landmarks, such as the Iolani Palace and the Bishop Museum.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Wild Reef
programme.desc: Experience the wonder of the Shedd Aquarium’s wild reef as light dances off the colorful aquatic sea life that peacefully swim past in the crystal-clear water. Ambient sound makes you feel as if you are deep beneath the ocean.

programme.title: Village of Swimming Cows
programme.desc: What happens when eco-minded, city-dwelling Berliners move in with Polish farmers in the country? Take a charming, extraordinarily funny look at how friendship and communication can overcome boundaries, and how nourishing the mind, body, and spirit begins with love and respect for Mother Earth.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Malta
programme.desc: A delightful Mediterranean climate, fantastic beaches, and fascinating historic sites only begin to describe the Maltese experience. Few places in the world possess a more exquisite coastline. The HBO series, "Game of Thrones," filmed portions of the series in Malta's capital city of Valletta.

programme.title: Dublin
programme.desc: At the confluence of Muir Eireann and the Irish Sea on Ireland’s East Coast stands the capital city of Dublin. Join Laura McKenzie as she enjoys the perfect pint at Gravity Bar atop Guinness Brewery, explore Dublin Castle, and become acquainted with The Four Seasons Dublin.

programme.title: Paris
programme.desc: There is more than enough to keep you busy in Paris. Historic sites such as the Louvre, Notre Dame Cathedral, the Picasso Museum, and Paris Opera House only get you started. Tuileries Garden and Paris Beach offer a unique way to relax and have fun, and Sacre-Coeur offers a 360-degree view of city.

programme.title: Los Angeles
programme.desc: Rent a Rolls Royce and roll through L.A. in style. When you hit Hollywood and Vine you know you are in the city’s heart, as the Pantages Theater, Capitol Records Building, Grauman's Chinese Theatre, and Kodak Theater greet you. Get the skinny on everything Beverly Hills and visit Olvera Street.

programme.title: Prague
programme.desc: Explore the heart of Bohemia as we join Laura in Prague. Visit Prague Castle, the Charles Bridge, and the Jewish Quarter. Gothic Loket Castle is a short, scenic drive away from the city and worth the tour. Next up the must-see spa town of Karlovy Vary.

programme.title: Britain's Historic Countryside
programme.desc: First stops are Camden Market and Notting Hill Gate. Enjoy a treat as Laura escorts you to the birthplace of pomp and circumstance, Buckingham Palace. Then mosey down to Windsor Castle before taking on London with Big Ben and Tower Bridge.

programme.title: S7E1 - Rome: Ancient Glory
programme.desc: Focusing on the grandeur of classical Rome, we’ll marvel at the Colosseum, Pantheon, and Capitoline Museum before heading out on a bike ride along the ancient Appian Way.

programme.title: S7E2 - Rome: Baroque Brilliance
programme.desc: As we ramble through the heart of Rome, we’ll admire breathtaking Bernini statues and ponder sunbeams inside St. Peter’s Basilica. After dinner, we’ll take a nighttime stroll, lacing together the city’s piazzas and fountains.

programme.title: S7E3 - Rome: Back-Street Riches
programme.desc: We explore Rome on a more intimate scale — dodging Vespas in Trastevere, roaming through the historic Jewish Ghetto, and enjoying art treasures in a string of rarely visited churches to uncover the charms of hidden Rome.

programme.title: S7E4 - Florence: Heart of the Renaissance
programme.desc: In Florence, we'll revel in the genius of Michelangelo and Botticelli, climb the dome that kicked off the Renaissance, and cross the Arno to take in modern-day artisan life.

programme.title: S7E5 - Florentine Delights and on exciting Tuscan Side Trips
programme.desc: We enjoy Renaissance art in Florence, the city that propelled Europe out of the Middle Ages. Then we visit two cultural capitals in their own right: Pisa, where we’ll marvel at a tipsy tower; and Lucca, where we’ll celebrate Puccini.

programme.title: S7E6 - Paris: Regal and Intimate
programme.desc: In Paris, we'll cruise the Seine River, pay a visit to Napoleon’s tomb, and take in the majestic Louvre. Then we'll shop in a village-like neighborhood, attend church in a pipe organ loft, and celebrate Bastille Day.

programme.title: S7E7 - Paris: Embracing Life and Art

programme.title: S7E8 - London: Historic and Dynamic
programme.desc: In London, we’ll ponder royal tombs in Westminster Abbey, discover treasures in the British Library, enjoy the vibrant evening scene in Soho, uncover Churchill’s secret WWII headquarters, and straddle the Prime Meridian at Greenwich.

programme.title: S7E9 - North England's Lake District and Durham
programme.desc: Hiking through the Cumbrian Lake District, we'll admire idyllic lakes, discover misty waterfalls, tour a slate mine, and climb up to a stony summit. Then we’ll play some cricket, hike Hadrian’s Wall, and be dazzled by Durham’s cathedral.

programme.title: S7E10 - Venice: City of Dreams
programme.desc: In Venice, we'll sample the splendor of the Doge's Palace, St. Mark's Basilica, Grand Canal, and masterpieces from the Venetian Renaissance — then take a glide on a gondola.

programme.title: S7E11 - Venice and Its Lagoon
programme.desc: We’ll start with a cruise through Venice’s lagoon, pausing to savor fresh fish canal-side. Then we’ll sample the treasures of the Accademia Gallery, explore some back-street wonders, and luxuriate in a venerable cafe on St. Mark’s Square.

programme.title: S7E12 - European Travel Skills Part 1
programme.desc: In this first of three shows focusing on European travel skills, we’ll visit the Netherlands and Germany to learn about transportation by train and car, changing money, and settling in upon arrival.

programme.title: S8E1 - Western Turkey

programme.title: S8E2 - Central Turkey

programme.title: Auckland

programme.title: Athens

programme.title: Singapore
programme.desc: The first sight is Singapore's Merlion statue. For glimpses of the wild you have three fun options where you can see exotic animals in their open (not closed) sanctuaries. Next, explore Raffles Landing for a picture-perfect view along the Singapore River.

programme.title: Naples
programme.desc: Naples exists in an incredible location at the base of Mt. Vesuvius beside the Port of Naples. Experience Napoli's castles on the islet of Megaris, Castel dell 'Ovo, Castel Nuovo, Castel Saint Elmo, Arch of Triumph of Alfonso, and the Torre dell' Oro.

programme.title: Gleneagles & Scottish Countryside

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Underwater Beauty
programme.desc: Fish of all stripes and fluorescence call the crystal-clear waters of Chicago’s Shedd Aquarium home. Water and light collaborate to reveal the tranquil beauty that is life underwater.

programme.title: Running of the Bulls
programme.desc: The Festival of San Fermin in Pamplona, Spain is a deeply rooted celebration of traditional and folkloric events, including the Running of the Bulls. Experience the incredible energy each morning for eight consecutive days as thousands of people run ahead of six, 2,000-pound charging bulls.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.
